<slurryPipeSystemPlaceableReference>

    <!-- ========================================================================
         FOLDER STRUCTURE
    =========================================================================

    configs/
    └── placeableConfigs/
        ├── PLACEABLE_REFERENCE.xml         ← this file
        ├── <placeableName>/
        │   ├── fillPoints.xml              ← placeable SPS config
        │   └── nodeTree.i3d               ← SPS nodes for this placeable
        └── ...

    The folder name under placeableConfigs/ must match the placeable's config
    filename (without .xml). The manager scans this folder name against loaded
    placeables at finalizePlacement time.

    Some placeables have variants that share a config — the manager matches by
    substring, so a folder named "cowShedUK" will match both "cowShedUK" and
    "cowShedUK_nonMilk". Use a subfolder for the non-milk variant if it requires
    a different fillPoints.xml.

    ======================================================================== -->


    <!-- ========================================================================
         NODE TREE — i3d SETUP
    =========================================================================

    All SPS nodes for a placeable are authored in a separate nodeTree i3d,
    typically named "nodeTree.i3d", placed alongside the placeable fillPoints.xml.

    The nodeTree is loaded via loadI3DFile at runtime and linked into the placeable
    scene hierarchy. It must have one root TransformGroup containing a single
    container child whose name matches an existing node in the placeable's own
    component hierarchy. The manager parents the nodeTree root into that node.

    Do NOT use cloneSharedI3DNode — cloning breaks skin bindings.

    ── FULL NODE TREE STRUCTURE ──────────────────────────────────────────────

    nodeTree root (TransformGroup)
    └── <containerName> (TransformGroup)     ← must match a node in the placeable i3d
        ├── pipeCouplers (TransformGroup)
        │   ├── SPS_pipeCoupler01            ← coupling 1 mount point
        │   │   └── SPS_pipeCoupler01Arcs
        │   │       ├── SPS_pipeCoupler01Arc01  ← arc detection node left
        │   │       └── SPS_pipeCoupler01Arc02  ← arc detection node right
        │   ├── SPS_pipeCoupler02            ← coupling 2 mount point (if needed)
        │   │   └── SPS_pipeCoupler02Arcs
        │   │       ├── SPS_pipeCoupler02Arc01
        │   │       └── SPS_pipeCoupler02Arc02
        │   └── (repeat for SPS_pipeCoupler03 etc. if required)
        │
        ├── fillPlaneNodes (TransformGroup)  ← detection nodes for fill plane shape
        │   ├── slurryPlaneCentre            ← centre of the fill area (all shapes)
        │   ├── slurryPlaneEdge              ← edge point — round shape only
        │   ├── slurryPlaneCorner1           ← first corner — rectangle shape only
        │   └── slurryPlaneCorner2           ← opposite corner — rectangle shape only
        │
        └── effects (TransformGroup)         ← inlet effect nodes (if used)
            └── effect (TransformGroup)      ← PipeEffect shape node
                └── pipeEffectSmoke          ← smoke/particle emitter

    ── NODE PLACEMENT RULES ──────────────────────────────────────────────────

    SPS_pipeCouplerXX
        Place at the physical centre of the coupling mouth on the building.
        Rotation: local Z-axis pointing outward away from the building wall.

    SPS_pipeCouplerXXArc01 / Arc02
        Place symmetrically either side of the coupler mouth:
            1.5m left and right in local X, 2.5m forward in local Z.
        These define the arc detection triangle. A vehicle or chain terminus
        must have overlapping arc nodes for a pipe connection to be offered.

    slurryPlaneCentre
        Place at ground level at the centre of the slurry pit or tank opening.
        Used as the XZ sampling position for surface height detection, and as
        the centre of the fill plane detection shape.

    slurryPlaneEdge (round shape only)
        Place at the edge of the circular pit at ground level.
        Distance from centre to edge defines the detection radius.
        A fill arm upper node must fall within this radius to register a connection.

    slurryPlaneCorner1 / slurryPlaneCorner2 (rectangle shape only)
        Place at two diagonally opposite corners of the rectangular pit at ground level.
        The rectangle they define is the detection zone for fill arm upper nodes.

    effect / pipeEffectSmoke
        Place at the physical inlet point where slurry enters the store —
        typically at the top of the inlet pipe or the pit opening.
        The PipeEffect streams visually from the connecting pipe end to this node.
        pipeEffectSmoke is repositioned dynamically as stream length changes.

    ── DEPLOYABLE COUPLING ANIM NODE ─────────────────────────────────────────

    When a coupling has deployable="true", the <pipeAnimNode> element in
    fillPoints.xml specifies a node in the placeable's own i3d (not the nodeTree)
    to rotate when the coupling is deployed. This is used to swing open a gate,
    lid or cover that conceals the coupling when it is not in use.

    The node is driven directly by SPS — it is not controlled by vanilla animation.
    rx, ry, rz are the Euler rotation in degrees applied when deployed.
    When undeployed the rotation is not modified — vanilla animation controls it.

    ======================================================================== -->


    <!-- ========================================================================
         FILL PLANE SURFACE DETECTION
    =========================================================================

    The fill plane determines two things:
        1. Whether a fill arm upper node is inside the store's fill area
           (confirms the arm is positioned over the correct store).
        2. The current slurry surface Y position used to check whether
           the arm lower node is submerged for flow to begin.

    Surface Y is read from the engine-managed fill plane node each tick.
    The fill plane node Y is driven by the engine based on current fill level,
    moving between minY (empty) and maxY (full) in the node's local space.
    SPS converts this to world Y via getWorldTranslation on the node.

    For STORAGE_PLANE sources (placeables) the surface Y is read directly
    from the fill plane node world translation — no getFillPlaneHeightAtLocalPos
    is used. The node must be the engine-animated fill plane shape.

    shape="round"
        Uses centreNode and edgeNode to define a circular detection zone.
        Radius = distance between centreNode and edgeNode at placement time.
        Fill arm upper node must fall within this radius in XZ to register.

    shape="rectangle"
        Uses centreNode, corner1Node and corner2Node to define a rectangle.
        Fill arm upper node must fall within the rectangle in XZ to register.

    If shape is omitted, no shape-based detection is used and connection is
    confirmed by the fill arm's own trigger volume check only.

    ======================================================================== -->


    <!-- ========================================================================
         PLACEABLE fillPoints.xml — ELEMENT REFERENCE
    =========================================================================

    ── <nodeTree> ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

    <nodeTree filename="nodeTree.i3d"/>

    filename    Path to the nodeTree i3d relative to this fillPoints.xml.

    ── <pipeAnimNode> ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

    <pipeAnimNode node="..." rx="N" ry="N" rz="N"/>

    node        Node name in the placeable's own i3d (not the nodeTree).
                This node is rotated when a deployable coupling on this
                placeable is deployed by the player.
    rx ry rz    Euler rotation in degrees applied to the node when deployed.
                When undeployed, SPS does not touch the node rotation —
                vanilla animation or default state controls it.

    Omit this element if the placeable has no deployable couplings, or if no
    visual rotation is needed when a coupling is deployed.

    ── <fillPlane> ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

    <fillPlane
        node="..."
        minY="N.N"
        maxY="N.N"
        fillType="..."
        shape="round|rectangle"
        centreNodeName="..."
        edgeNodeName="..."
        corner1NodeName="..."
        corner2NodeName="..."
    />

    node            Engine-animated fill plane node name in the placeable i3d.
                    The engine moves this node's Y between minY and maxY as
                    the storage fills and empties.
    minY            Local Y of the fill plane node when the storage is empty.
    maxY            Local Y of the fill plane node when the storage is full.
    fillType        Fill type string for this storage (e.g. LIQUIDMANURE).

    shape="round"       Circular arm detection zone.
                        Requires: centreNodeName, edgeNodeName.
    shape="rectangle"   Rectangular arm detection zone.
                        Requires: centreNodeName, corner1NodeName, corner2NodeName.

    centreNodeName  Node in the nodeTree at the centre of the fill area.
    edgeNodeName    Node at the edge of the fill area — round shape only.
    corner1NodeName First corner of the rectangle — rectangle shape only.
    corner2NodeName Diagonally opposite corner — rectangle shape only.

    ── <pipeCouplings> ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────

    <pipeCouplings>
        <pipeCoupling
            id="N"
            mountNodeName="..."
            flowDirection="DISCHARGE|FILL|BOTH"
            valveType="MANUAL|HYDRAULIC|NONE"
            deployable="bool"
            maxPipeLength="N.N"
        >
            <effects inletDistance="N.N">
                <effectNode ... />
            </effects>
        </pipeCoupling>
    </pipeCouplings>

    id              Unique integer ID for this coupling within the placeable.

    mountNodeName   Node name of the coupling mount point in the nodeTree.
                    Arc detection nodes must exist as children named:
                        <mountNodeName>Arcs
                            <mountNodeName>Arc01
                            <mountNodeName>Arc02

    flowDirection
        DISCHARGE   Only allows slurry to be pumped INTO this store.
                    Vehicles cannot pull slurry out via this coupling.
                    The conduit pump respects this — it will not pull from
                    a DISCHARGE-only coupling regardless of its direction setting.
        FILL        Only allows slurry to be pulled OUT of this store.
        BOTH        No restriction — flow in either direction is permitted.

    valveType
        MANUAL      Valve is opened by the player at the coupling using long press R.
        HYDRAULIC   Valve is cab-controlled — no manual valve interaction at coupling.
        NONE        No valve — flow begins immediately when connected and pump is on.
                    Standard for placeable store couplings where the store itself
                    does not have a physical valve.

    deployable      true = coupling is hidden by default on the placeable.
                    Player deploys it via long press R when within range.
                    Use for couplings that are only needed occasionally,
                    e.g. a pipe port concealed on a building wall.
                    Pair with <pipeAnimNode> to rotate a cover or gate on deploy.

    maxPipeLength   Maximum distance in metres for a bez pipe or chain terminus
                    to connect to this coupling. Typical: 4.0–8.0.
                    Omit to allow connection at any distance.

    <effects> (optional child of <pipeCoupling>)
        Declares the visual inlet effect played when slurry flows into this coupling.

        inletDistance   Stream length in metres from the pipe end to the inlet.
                        Set to match the physical distance from the coupling mount
                        node to where slurry visually enters the store.

        <effectNode
            effectClass="PipeEffect"    Must be PipeEffect for slurry stream visuals.
            effectNode="..."            Node name in the nodeTree for the PipeEffect shape.
            materialType="pipe"         Use "pipe" for slurry pipe effect material.
            maxBending="N.N"            Maximum pipe bending factor (0.0–1.0).
            extraDistance="N.N"         Extra stream distance added to the inlet offset.
            positionUpdateNodes="..."   Space-separated node names to reposition as
                                        stream length updates (e.g. pipeEffectSmoke).
        />
        <effectNode
            effectNode="..."            Node name of the secondary smoke/particle effect.
            materialType="unloadingSmoke"
            startDelay="N.N"            Seconds before this effect starts after flow begins.
            alignToWorldY="true"        Keeps the emitter aligned to world up axis.
        />

    ── <hideNodes> ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

    <hideNodes>
        <node name="..."/>
    </hideNodes>

    Lists nodes in the placeable i3d to hide when SPS is active on this placeable.
    Use to suppress vanilla drive-in trigger meshes, fill towers, ramps or any
    geometry that conflicts with SPS pipe connections.
    Node names must match i3dMapping ids or node names in the placeable i3d.

    ── <hideCollisions> ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────

    <hideCollisions>
        <node name="..."/>
    </hideCollisions>

    Lists collision nodes in the placeable i3d to disable when SPS is active.
    Use to remove vanilla drive-in ramp collisions or fill tower collision bodies
    that would block vehicle access or interfere with pipe placement.

    ======================================================================== -->

</slurryPipeSystemPlaceableReference>
